<title>USA: Celadon files for employee stock plan.</title>
<headline>Celadon files for employee stock plan.</headline>
<dateline>INDIANAPOLIS 1996-10-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Celadon Group Inc said Friday it filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission a plan to allow employees to purchase stock in the company.</p>
<p>The plan, called Celadon Hallmark Investment Plan, will allow employees, with the exception of executives, to set aside up to 10 percent of each paycheck to purchase Celadon stock.</p>
<p>Under the plan, employees can purchase stock at a discount. Shares will be purchased on a quarterly basis by Furman Selz LLC.</p>
<p>Celadon specializes in transporting truckloads of goods to and from Mexico.</p>
<p>Reuters Chicago Newsdesk - 312-408-8787</p>
